<TEXT>
the new government sunday approved the 
nomination of zalman shoval as its ambassador to the united states 
a foreign ministry spokesman said 
shoval 60 a legislator from prime minister yitzhak shamirs 
rightwing likud bloc will resign from the parliament or knesset 
before assuming his post the spokesman said 
the replacement will take effect at the end of september after 
the us administration agrees to the nomination in accordance with 
diplomatic protocol he said 
shoval himself speaking on israel army radio expressed hope he 
would encounter a more positive atmosphere in washington than did 
his predecessor moshe arad 
the us administration has been increasingly critical of the 
jewish state over its failed peace efforts with the palestinians 
they have been waging a 32month rebellion against israeli 
occupation of the west bank and the gaza strip 
shoval said the us administration due to the persian gulf 
crisis now appears to realize that the israelipalestinian 
conflict is not the main reason for conflict in the middle east and 
that israel is in the end the only stable ally the united states 
has in the middle east 
the polishborn shoval is an veteran israeli politician who is 
also experienced in diplomacy in 19551957 he worked at the 
foreign ministry where he rose from a cadet to the post of deputy 
head of the north american desk 
</TEXT>
