1949 until the wall went up the barrier watched over by armed 
guards with shoot to kill orders reduced that flow to a 
trickle more than 200 east germans were killed trying to escape to 
the west across the barrier that snaked through berlin and along 
the border with west germany 
on nov 9 1989 the reform communists who ousted hardliner 
erich honecker opened the wall in a lastditch effort to retain 
power they had hoped to stem a flood of east germans to west 
germany that had reached more than 200000 
by the end of this year east and west germany plan to merge to 
form one country 
east germans enjoyed the most prosperous economy in the soviet 
bloc but now face a major challenge in trying to catch up with the 
