that would be in addition to an existing quota of 22 percent for 
low caste hindus and tribes in public service and higher education 
jobs according to a list drawn up after india became independent 
in 1947 and included in the constitution the quota has never been 
filled completely 
if the governments plan is carried out 49 percent of 
government jobs will be set aside for low castes and 51 percent 
will be awarded purely on merit 
