jobs for people from disadvantaged classes defined by their 
income social position and education 
according to the sunday observer newspaper the disadvantaged 
castes identified by the commission comprise 437 percent of the 
population or about 385 million people 
in indias highly structured society hundreds of castes and 
subcastes have been delineated in a strict hierarchy by thousands 
of years of hindu tradition 
modern india an avowedly secular nation whose population is 82 
percent hindu is pledged to discard the caste system and build an 
egalitarian state 
but the caste system persists particularly in rural areas 
dictating rules of behavior occupation and association 
