negotiations broke down over a new contract to replace the one 
currey had negotiated in 1987 
three months into the strike greyhound filed for bankruptcy 
court protection from its creditors blaming increased legal and 
security costs required to combat the initially violent walkout 
the bankruptcy remains in its early stages with current 
management still running the company no reorganization plan is due 
until october and since extensions on initial plan deadlines are 
frequently granted greyhound spokesman george gravley says the 
companys plan should be ready by early november 
