greyhound streamlined somewhat 
our strategy at operating this business turned around a dying 
business he said so a reorganization plan will employ exactly 
the same strategies updated and enhanced that we employed 
before the bankruptcy 
currey a career bus executive led a team of investors in 1987 
that paid 270 million for the bus operations of greyhound corp 
since renamed greyhound dial corp a few months later the 
investors plunked down another 80 million for dallasbased 
trailways lines inc the largest trailways franchisee 
after merging the two operations currey ran the nations only 
intercity bus company 
ridership had been falling each year before the buyout 
bottoming out at 609 billion passenger miles in 1986 after the 
buyout ridership increased each year hitting 748 billion 
passenger miles in 1989 
greyhound also turned its first profit that year earning 
730000 on about 1 billion in revenues after losing about 20 
million over the previous two years 
