<TEXT>
western union corp on saturday 
locked out 2000 employees in the middle of contract talks with 
their union 
the company did not indicate whether the workers would be 
rehired if it signs a new contract with their union the 
communications workers of america which represents a total of 
2500 workers at western union 
western union said the replacements would not affect its 
moneytransfer telex electronic mail and paperbased message 
services 
we sincerely regret that in the absence of a union contract 
we have reluctantly had to take this defensive action said 
robert j amman western union president and chief executive 
officer we cannot operate under the everpresent threat of an 
employee strike while continuing to bear the cost required to 
ensure that the company would survive one 
western union has a total of 16000 employees about half the 
employees represented by cwa are recording operators and the 
others are mostly customer relations clerks clerical workers and 
field technicians 
dan beckstead the chief union negotiator deplored the lockout 
saying the union had not given the company any indication it 
intends to strike 
in fact we told them we wanted to continue to negotiate in an 
attempt to reach an agreement beckstead said cwa workers have 
authorized their leadership to call a strike 
western union said many of the replaced cwa workers were from 
its central telephone bureaus in bridgeton miss and reno nev 
its computer centers in middletown va and bridgeton 
it temporarily replaced them with workers from western union 
headquarters and trained temporary replacements the company said 
the company has been negotiating with representatives of the cwa 
since july 23 the previous twoyear contract expired aug 6 but 
management and union negotiators have continued to meet to try to 
agree on a new pact 
management on aug 8 proposed a 90day extension of the old 
contract but the offer was rejected by the cwa 
the contract issues include wages health care and job 
classifications as well as western unions right to use outside 
contractors and hire parttime workers the operators average about 
10 an hour 
beckstead said western union has not responded to the unions 
latest offer made friday the company however said the union had 
until midnight sunday to agree to a 90day contract extension 
